$ System.Data.DataSet (class)

`System.Data.DataSet` is an in-memory cache of relational and persistent → development/Data and a major component of the → Microsoft/dot-net/ADO architecture.

Because a `DataSet` stores data in-memory, it allows for ADO.NET's *disconnected programming model*.

A `DataSet` object consists of multiple → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/DataTable[`System.Data.DataTable`s] that are possibly related in parent-child relationships through
→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/DataRelation[`System.Data.DataRelation`] objects.

It is possible to define *constraints* on the tables.

A `DataSet` might be connected to a persistent → development/Data source with a → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/Common/DataAdapter[`System.Data.Common.DataAdapter`].

Important properties:
  • `SelectCommand `
  • `InsertCommand`
  • `UpdateCommand`
  • `DeleteCommand`

`Fill()` uses the value of `SelectCommand` to transfer data into a `DataSet`.

sa:
  Compare with → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/DataTable[`System.Data.DataTable`]
